  "name": "Building Blocks - ILIAD API Profiles",
  "abstract": "(Under construction) - defines and demonstrates a reusable mechanism for specialisation of OGC APIs using the Oceans Information Model (OIM) for semantic interoperability.",
  "description": "Each building block defines a profile of a data exchange schema based on OGC API responses, mapped to the OIM using JSON-LD contexts. Common patterns are factored into reusable foundations to simplify development and maximise interoperability of such profiles, in a way which is scalable across future application requirements. \n\nThus, a pilot project to monitor Jellyfish swarms using Citizen Science will reuse common patterns for Citizen Science observations, which in turn we reuse a common pattern for observations, using an underlying component of the OIM - the OGC Observations model (SOSA ontology). \n",
  "modified": "2026-04-17T11:12:50.527530",
  "tooling": {
    "bblocks-postprocess": {
      "commitId": "\"82fc8650df6a65be1e17f7c6440191f0b7c6ccff",
